data.text:
April 29, 1937 was a Thursday and it was the 119th day of the year 1937 in the Gregorian calendar.

April 29, 1937 can also be written as 4/29/1937 in the US and as 29/4/1937 in UK and Europe.

The Zodiac and Astrological sign for April 29th is Taurus.

Taurus is the 2nd sign in the Western Zodiac. People born between April 20th and May 20th belong to the Taurus sign: discover Taurus personality and who should a Taurus marry.

Moon phase

The moon phase on April 29, 1937 was Waning gibbous.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on April 29, 1937 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on April 29, 1937 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 79% full, rising at 10:53 pm and setting at 09:16 am.

The previous full moon was on Apr 25, 1937 while the next full moon would come on May 25, 1937.

What is special about April 29th?

April 29th refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 29th day of the month of April. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.

Over the years several events happened on April 29th, such as:

2019 - A propaganda video featuring abu bakr al baghdadi, leader of islamic state of iraq, is released. it refers to the 2019 sri lanka easter bombings. this indicates that he is still alive, and that the video was taken very recently. this is his first appearance on video since july 2014 when he spoke to a crowd at the now demolished great mosque of al-nuri, mosul.

2018 - Israel defense forces arrested a hamas suspect for tampering at the karni crossing on the israeli-gazan frontier.

2017 - North korea and weapons-of-mass destruction: u.s. pacific command officials and south korean defense officials reported that a north korean missile had been fired early in the morning. however, it quickly failed to travel beyond north korea. this is similar to a failed attempt by north korea 13 days ago.
